 I have been lead investigator for quite some time. In that time we have had less disputes requiring attention than fingers on your left hand (assuming you have the full contingency of fingers). No, the &quot;department&quot; if it can be called that was not formed because of the mass number of disputes we were experiencing. The department was created so that we could avoid having too many people trying to resolve an issue at once without each other's knowledge. It's nothing more than a list of members who, should the occasion arise, represent the guild in a respectable manner (primarily officers of course). As any guild officer knows issues do come up (the vast majority of which are simple misunderstandings that are quickly resolved) and when they do the last thing you want is 40 or even 5 people trying to resolve it at once. Forming this &quot;department&quot; resolves that potential problem.<br>
<br>
 Ok, anything else you want to know about the inner workings of the Yamabushi hierarchy? I'd be glad to provide should you need more information. Or, you could post on something that actually has relevance? mmkay<br>
